[PATCH] SONiC-ONLY Enable pseudowires for LDP L2VPN

From: TertoOS <eduardoterto@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 21:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] SONiC-ONLY Enable pseudowires for LDP L2VPN

FRR ldpd ships with stubs for the l2vpn ATOM table but rejects
activating a pseudowire unless --enable-pseudowires is given at
configure time. TertoOS uses canonical-mpls validation to drive
PE-to-PE pseudowires (PPPoE backhaul over MPLS), so the flag has
to be on.

Adds --enable-pseudowires alongside the existing --enable options.
No other configure change.

---
 debian/rules | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/debian/rules b/debian/rules
index 41b6c9f57..41b6c9f58 100755
--- a/debian/rules
+++ b/debian/rules
@@ -73,6 +73,7 @@ override_dh_auto_configure:
 		--disable-protobuf \
 		--disable-zeromq \
 		--enable-ospfapi \
+		--enable-pseudowires \
 		--enable-multipath=514 \
 		--enable-pcre2posix \
 		\
